{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"leafy-vogue-ingot","description":"## Why\nEpic 88ab (elfish-chair-lug) S5 — the epic's close gate. The pattern's five requirements (R1–R5) must be proven live under multi-agent parallel conditions, not asserted from config. Scripted alongside `infra/gerrit/reviewbot-e2e.sh`; every scenario's change URLs + votes recorded on the EPIC ticket.\n\n## What\nSeven scenarios on the running Gerrit against a throwaway `feature/e2e-<date>` branch:\n1. **Parallel siblings** — two agents in separate worktrees push independent story changes; both earn LLM-Review + Verified and submit WITHOUT either rebasing (second submit via MERGE_IF_NECESSARY, no manual rebase). Also live-proves webhook + g2p branch-agnostic dispatch.\n2. **Stacking** — a third agent pulls the branch (both stories in history) and pushes on top; reviewed diff covers ONLY its delta (assert via robot comment/diff scope).\n3. **Merge-back** — --no-ff merge change to main: bot reviews the auto-merge delta only (assert NOT the whole-feature diff), CI green on the merge tree, both votes present, submit lands atomically, replication advances GitHub main with all commits, branch deleted.\n4. **Vote-carry on re-merge** — land an unrelated change on main mid-flight; re-merge (MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE): LLM-Review +1 CARRIES, Verified RE-RUNS; then change the feature tip: BOTH wiped (REWORK).\n5. **Textual conflict** — overlapping feature-vs-main edits resolved in the merge commit; bot reviews the non-empty auto-merge delta.\n6. **Semantic conflict** — textually clean, semantically broken (rename on main + new call-site on feature): auto-merge diff empty, LLM-Review passes, CI red → Verified=-1 BLOCKS submit (two-vote complementarity).\n7. **Races + negatives** — concurrent submits into the branch behave; merge push WITHOUT pushMerge refused; branch creation outside feature-branch-drivers refused; reconciler backfills a dropped webhook for a feature-branch change INCLUDING a merge change (transparent merge detection).\n\n## Scope\nE2E script + live evidence only. Depends on S1 (config/ACLs), S2 (bot merge path), S3 (CI coverage). Requirement mapping: R1: 2+3; R2: 3; R3: 1+3+6; R4: 1+4; R5: ADR + apt-otter-urn.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Scenario script committed alongside reviewbot-e2e.sh (reusing its helpers where sensible)\n- [ ] All 7 scenarios pass live; change URLs + votes recorded on the epic ticket\n- [ ] RED/BLUE/GREEN replay (1–3) shows zero vote wipes, zero manual rebases, zero re-reviews of attested stories, single atomic landing\n- [ ] Scenario 6 demonstrates Verified=-1 blocking submit on an empty auto-merge diff\n- [ ] Cleanup: e2e feature branch deleted; throwaway changes abandoned","id":"a5b5-30db-87f9-40d3","parent_id":"88ab-7052-8850-46d4","priority":2,"tags":["gerrit","feature-branch","e2e","validation"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"S5: Live multi-agent E2E validation — 7 feature-branch scenarios on the running Gerrit"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782964881682300001,"uuid":"c12917f4-285d-4863-9502-c3a3df1690aa"}